    /// on the two named cardinality peers, without allocating either
    /// `Vec<ConfigTierKind>`), and `map.contributing_tiers().len()
    /// == 1 || map.absent_tiers().len() == 1` (the dual-`Vec`
    /// equality form, which allocates *two* `Vec<ConfigTierKind>`
    /// values just to peek their lengths). The four forms drifted in
    /// subtle ways at every consumer site (allocation vs. scalar,
    /// turbofish vs. name-only, support side vs. coverage-gap side,
    /// structural disjunction vs. dual-equality arithmetic). This
    /// lift names the singular-tier-counts predicate directly at the
    /// tier-altitude surface with a single-pass short-circuiting
    /// scan — the typed boolean every operator-facing *"did the fold
    /// land one tier off the coverage boundary?"* check reads off as
    /// a single method call.
    ///
    /// The tier-altitude singular-predicate peer that **climbs the
    /// "singular across altitudes" projection** from the diff
    /// altitude seeded by [`ConfigDiff::kinds_singular`]. The
    /// pattern is the same at every altitude: fuse the four
    /// documented open-coded surface forms (union-of-singular-
    /// boundaries disjunction, support-scalar dual-equality, dual-
    /// scalar equality, dual-`Vec` dual-equality) into a single
    /// boolean predicate named at the surface, routed through the
    /// shared [`crate::AxisHistogram::has_singular`] primitive one
    /// altitude down. The chain altitude's three sub-axes
    /// (`layer_kinds_singular`, `file_formats_singular`,
    /// `env_prefix_kinds_singular` over the corresponding chain
    /// histograms) are the natural next sideways lifts. Completes
    /// the middle-leg-corner of the distance-from-boundary ternary
    /// partition `(has_boundary, has_singular,
    /// has_strict_partial_cover)` at the tier altitude — the
    /// vertical peer of the just-closed magnitude-direction ternary
    /// `(tiers_low_support, tiers_strict_partial_cover,
    /// tiers_high_support)` on the same 5-corner support-
    /// cardinality partition, the two orthogonal ternary refinements
    /// on the same altitude.
    ///
    /// **Cardinality-`4` reachability at the tier altitude — every
    /// leg non-vacuously inhabited.** [`ConfigTierKind`] carries
    /// four cells so the two singular boundaries sit at support
    /// cardinalities `1` and `3`, disjoint from each other AND from
    /// the strict-interior support cardinality `2` and the two
    /// boundary cardinalities `0` and `4`. Every fold observing one
    /// tier (support `1`) reads `true` via `tiers_singular_support`;
    /// every fold observing three tiers (support `3`) reads `true`
    /// via `tiers_singular_gap`; every fold observing zero, two, or
    /// four tiers reads `false`. Strict advance over the diff
    /// altitude: on the cardinality-`3` `DiffLineKind` axis the
    /// strict-interior leg vanishes (interval `[2, 1]` is empty), so
    /// `kinds_singular ⇔ (kinds_any_observed && !kinds_full_cover)`
    /// pointwise; at the tier altitude the strict-interior fold
    /// (two-tier partial cover) lifts the equivalence to
    /// `tiers_singular ⇔ (tiers_any_observed && !tiers_full_cover)
    /// && !tiers_strict_partial_cover` verbatim — the distance
    /// ternary closes strictly *and* non-vacuously with content on
    /// every leg.
    ///
    /// **Empty-map convention** — returns `false` on the empty map:
    /// the empty map observes zero cells, so all four cells are
    /// unobserved (four zeros on the cardinality-`4` axis) — neither
    /// `tiers_singular_support` (nonzeros `== 1`) nor
    /// `tiers_singular_gap` (zeros `== 1`) fires. Matches
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::has_singular`]'s empty-histogram
    /// `false` convention one altitude down for every cardinality-
    /// `>= 2` axis. The empty map sits on the disjoint bottom
    /// coverage boundary of the distance-from-boundary ternary
    /// partition, carried by `has_boundary` (via
    /// `!tiers_any_observed`) instead. Matches
    /// [`ConfigDiff::kinds_singular`]'s empty-diff `false` polarity
    /// on the diff altitude in the same projection.
    ///
    /// **Singleton-support convention** — returns `true` on every
    /// fold whose observed support is a single [`ConfigTierKind`]
    /// cell: the support cardinality is `1` (three unobserved cells
    /// on the cardinality-`4` axis), so `tiers_singular_support`
    /// fires and the disjunction holds via that disjunct. Every fold
    /// with all leaves attributed to only-`Bare`, only-`Discovered`,
    /// only-`Default`, or only-`Custom` is a witness on the `true`
    /// side. Direct witness of the subsumption
    /// `tiers_singular_support ⇒ tiers_singular` on every axis with
    /// cardinality `>= 2`.
    ///
    /// **Two-tier partial cover convention** — returns `false` on
    /// every fold whose observed support is exactly two
    /// [`ConfigTierKind`] cells: the support cardinality is `2` (two
    /// unobserved cells on the cardinality-`4` axis), so neither
    /// `tiers_singular_support` (nonzeros `== 2 ≠ 1`) nor
    /// `tiers_singular_gap` (zeros `== 2 ≠ 1`) fires — the two-tier
    /// partial-cover fixture is the unique strict-interior witness
    /// on the cardinality-`4` tier axis, sitting on the disjoint
    /// [`Self::tiers_strict_partial_cover`] leg of the distance
    /// ternary. Distinguishes the tier altitude from the diff
    /// altitude, where two-kind partial cover falls on the singleton-
    /// gap boundary (support size `axis_cardinality - 1 = 2`) and
    /// lands on the `true` side.
    ///
    /// **Three-tier partial cover convention** — returns `true` on
    /// every fold whose observed support is exactly three
    /// [`ConfigTierKind`] cells: one cell is unobserved (four total
    /// minus three observed equals one unobserved), exactly the
    /// singleton-gap boundary, so `tiers_singular_gap` fires and the
    /// disjunction holds via that disjunct. A fold observing only
    /// the `Bare`, `Default`, and `Custom` tiers is a witness:
    /// `Discovered` is silent, satisfying the singular-gap. Direct
    /// witness of the subsumption `tiers_singular_gap ⇒
    /// tiers_singular` on every axis via the singleton-gap disjunct
    /// of the defining union.
    ///
    /// **Uniform four-tier cover convention** — returns `false` on
    /// every fold where each [`ConfigTierKind`] cell was observed at
    /// least once: the support cardinality is `4` (no unobserved
    /// cells), so `tiers_singular_gap` fails (`zeros == 0 ≠ 1`) and
    /// `tiers_singular_support` fails (`nonzeros == 4 ≠ 1`). The
    /// full-cover boundary sits at the top of the coverage interval,
    /// one of the two boundary corners carried by `has_boundary`
    /// (via `tiers_full_cover`) in the distance ternary — disjoint
    /// from the singular near-boundary corner.
    ///
    /// # Invariants
    ///
    /// - `tiers_singular() == tier_histogram().has_singular()` —
    ///   both project the same predicate off the same primitive;
    ///   the named seam is the cube-native routing of the histogram
    ///   surface.
    /// - `tiers_singular() ⇔ tiers_singular_support() ||
    ///   tiers_singular_gap()` — the defining union-of-singular-
    ///   boundaries disjunction on the two named histogram-side
    ///   peers. The singular near-boundary corner folds the two
    ///   singular-cardinality boundaries into one named one-cell-
    ///   off-boundary corner without discarding the finer resolution
    ///   below.
    /// - `tiers_singular() == (contributing_tiers_count() == 1 ||
    ///   contributing_tiers_count() ==
    ///   crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>() - 1)` always —
    ///   the support-scalar dual-equality surface, without
    ///   allocating either `Vec<ConfigTierKind>`. On the cardinality-
    ///   `4` tier axis the two equalities are disjoint (`1 ≠ 3 =
    ///   cardinality - 1`) and the disjunction reads the true dual.
    /// - `tiers_singular() == (contributing_tiers_count() == 1 ||
    ///   absent_tiers_count() == 1)` always — the dual-scalar
    ///   equality form on the two named cardinality peers, the
    ///   `contributing + absent == axis_cardinality` invariant
    ///   restated. Peer of the histogram-side dual-scalar equality
    ///   form `hist.distinct_cells() == 1 ||
    ///   hist.unobserved_cells() == 1` pinned one altitude down.
    /// - `tiers_singular_support() ⇒ tiers_singular()` always — the
    ///   subsumption via the `tiers_singular_support` disjunct of
    ///   the defining union. The singleton-support boundary always
    ///   sits inside the singular near-boundary corner.
    /// - `tiers_singular_gap() ⇒ tiers_singular()` always — the
    ///   subsumption via the `tiers_singular_gap` disjunct of the
    ///   defining union. The singleton-gap boundary always sits
    ///   inside the singular near-boundary corner.
    /// - `tiers_singular() ⇒ tiers_any_observed()` on every axis
    ///   with cardinality `>= 2`: both disjuncts require at least
    ///   one observed cell (`singular_support` has nonzeros `>= 1`;
    ///   `singular_gap` has nonzeros `= cardinality - 1 >= 1`).
    ///   Empty-map subsumption on the bottom coverage boundary.
    /// - `tiers_singular() ⇒ !tiers_full_cover()` on every axis with
    ///   cardinality `>= 2`: `tiers_singular_support` has support
    ///   `1 < cardinality`, `tiers_singular_gap` has support
    ///   `cardinality - 1 < cardinality`. Full-cover disjointness on
    ///   the top coverage boundary.
    /// - `tiers_singular() ⇒ !tiers_strict_partial_cover()` always —
    ///   the two named corners of the distance-from-boundary ternary
    ///   are pairwise disjoint. Carries content at the tier altitude
    ///   (the two-tier partial-cover fixture witnesses
    ///   `tiers_strict_partial_cover == true` and `tiers_singular ==
    ///   false`), unlike the vacuously-`true` consequent on the
    ///   cardinality-`3` diff altitude where the strict interior is
    ///   empty. Peer of the histogram-side
    ///   `axis_histogram_has_boundary_has_singular_has_strict_partial_cover_form_strict_ternary_partition_for_every_closed_axis_implementor`
    ///   partition law one altitude down.
    /// - `!tiers_any_observed() || tiers_full_cover() ⇒
    ///   !tiers_singular()` on every axis with cardinality `>= 2`:
    ///   the two boundary corners carried by `has_boundary` in the
    ///   distance ternary are disjoint from the singular near-
    ///   boundary corner. Direct pin of the partition edge from the
    ///   boundary leg into the singular leg — the two singular
    ///   cardinalities (`1` and `cardinality - 1`) sit strictly
    ///   between the two boundary cardinalities (`0` and
    ///   `cardinality`).
    /// - `(!tiers_any_observed() || tiers_full_cover(), tiers_singular,
    ///   tiers_strict_partial_cover)` is a strict ternary partition
    ///   on every axis with cardinality `>= 2` (every tier-altitude
    ///   implementor today — [`ConfigTierKind`] carries four cells).
    ///   Exactly one leg fires on every fold — the distance-from-
    ///   boundary ternary of the 5-corner support-cardinality
    ///   partition, folding the two boundary corners (empty and
    ///   full-cover) into `has_boundary`, the two singular near-
    ///   boundary corners into `has_singular`, and the boundary-free
    ///   strict interior into `has_strict_partial_cover`. Every leg
    ///   is inhabited at the tier altitude (empty-map / uniform
    ///   four-tier cover fixtures witness the boundary leg,
    ///   singleton-support / three-tier partial cover fixtures
    ///   witness the singular leg, the two-tier partial-cover
    ///   fixture witnesses the strict-interior leg) — a strict
    ///   advance over the diff altitude's degenerate two-way partition
    ///   `(!kinds_any_observed || kinds_full_cover, kinds_singular)`.
    /// - **Cross-surface bridge law** —
    ///   `map.tiers_singular() ==
    ///    map.tier_histogram().support_cardinality_class().is_singular()`
    ///   always. The class-side projection lands on
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularSupport`] or
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularGap`] exactly when
    ///   the histogram-side disjunction fires, and
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::is_singular`] reads
    ///   `true` on either variant. Peer of the histogram-side bridge
    ///   `axis_histogram_has_singular_agrees_with_class_is_singular_for_every_closed_axis_implementor`
    ///   one altitude down, closing the (histogram, class) duality
    ///   on the singular near-boundary leg at the tier altitude.
    ///
    /// # Cost
    ///
    /// `O(n + k)` where `n = self.inner.len()` (the histogram
    /// build) and `k = crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()`
    /// (the singular scan). Both are `O(n)` in practice since the
    /// tier axis carries a fixed four-cell cardinality; the returned
    /// `bool` reads one predicate. The scan short-circuits the
    /// *moment* both a *second* zero count *and* a *second* nonzero
    /// count have been witnessed (bounded at four witness cells
    /// visited on any strict-interior histogram), strictly tighter
    /// than the four documented open-coded surfaces — no boolean
    /// disjunction across two named predicates with two full walks
    /// of the counts vector, no [`crate::axis_cardinality`]
    /// turbofish with `- 1` arithmetic against a magic threshold, no
    /// `Vec<ConfigTierKind>` allocation.
    #[must_use]
    pub fn tiers_singular(&self) -> bool {
        self.tier_histogram().has_singular()
    }

    /// Returns `true` when this fold's observed [`ConfigTierKind`]
    /// support sits on a *coverage boundary* — either every tier cell
    /// unobserved ([`Self::tiers_any_observed`] `== false`) or every
    /// tier cell observed at least once ([`Self::tiers_full_cover`]
    /// `== true`).
    ///
    /// The **boundary-tier-counts boolean predicate** on the tier
    /// altitude, the top-leg corner of the distance-from-boundary
    /// ternary partition `(has_boundary, has_singular,
    /// has_strict_partial_cover)` — folding the two extreme coverage-
    /// cardinality corners (support cardinality `0` and
    /// `axis_cardinality`) into a single named on-boundary corner
    /// without discarding the finer resolution below. Routes through
    /// [`Self::tier_histogram`]`::has_boundary`, the single-pass
    /// short-circuiting scan over the fixed-cardinality counts vector
    /// that returns `false` the moment both a zero cell *and* a
    /// nonzero cell have been witnessed, bounded at two witness cells
    /// — strictly tighter than any of the documented open-coded
    /// surfaces one seam over.
    ///
    /// The **boundary-tier-counts peer** of the two documented surface
    /// forms consumers previously re-derived inline:
    /// `!map.tiers_any_observed() || map.tiers_full_cover()` (the
    /// defining union-of-coverage-boundaries disjunction on the two
    /// named histogram-side peers — one negation and two method calls
    /// with a boolean or), and
    /// `map.contributing_tiers_count() == 0 ||
    /// map.contributing_tiers_count() ==
    /// crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()` (the support-
    /// scalar dual-equality form, which pays for a full-axis scan and
    /// equates a `usize` against two magic thresholds with a
    /// turbofish). This lift names the boundary-tier-counts predicate
    /// directly at the tier-altitude surface with a single-pass short-
    /// circuiting scan — the typed boolean every operator-facing
    /// *"did the fold land on a coverage boundary?"* check reads off
    /// as a single method call.
    ///
    /// The tier-altitude boundary-predicate peer that **climbs the
    /// "boundary across altitudes" projection** — the top-leg corner
    /// of the distance-from-boundary ternary partition
    /// `(has_boundary, has_singular, has_strict_partial_cover)` at
    /// the tier altitude, lifting the diff-altitude seed
    /// [`ConfigDiff::kinds_boundary`] one altitude up alongside the
    /// already-closed middle-leg [`Self::tiers_singular`] projection
    /// and the already-closed bottom-leg
    /// [`Self::tiers_strict_partial_cover`] projection. The natural
    /// next lifts fan sideways along the chain altitude's three sub-
    /// axes ([`crate::ConfigSourceChain::layer_kinds_boundary`],
    /// [`crate::ConfigSourceChain::file_formats_boundary`],
    /// [`crate::ConfigSourceChain::env_prefix_kinds_boundary`] over
    /// the corresponding chain histograms). The pattern is the same
    /// at every altitude / sub-axis: fuse the documented open-coded
    /// surface forms (union-of-coverage-boundaries disjunction,
    /// support-scalar dual-equality) into a single boolean predicate
    /// named at the surface, routed through the shared
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::has_boundary`] primitive one altitude
    /// down.
    ///
    /// **Cardinality-`4` reachability at the tier altitude — the
    /// coverage boundary carries non-vacuous witnesses on both
    /// sides.** [`ConfigTierKind`] carries four cells, so
    /// `tiers_boundary()` reads `true` on the empty map (four
    /// unobserved cells — empty disjunct) and on every uniform four-
    /// tier cover (four observed cells — full-cover disjunct), and
    /// `false` on every singleton-support fold (support cardinality
    /// `1` — one nonzero and three zeros mixed), on every two-tier
    /// partial cover (support cardinality `2` — two nonzeros and two
    /// zeros mixed), and on every three-tier partial cover (support
    /// cardinality `3` — three nonzeros and one zero mixed). Non-
    /// vacuous on both sides of the coverage boundary at the tier
    /// altitude, matching the diff altitude on the same shape and
    /// leaving three off-boundary support cardinalities inhabited
    /// (rather than two on the cardinality-`3` diff axis).
    ///
    /// **Empty-map convention** — returns `true` on the empty map:
    /// the empty map observes zero cells, so every cell is unobserved
    /// (four zeros on the cardinality-`4` axis) — the single-pass
    /// scan sees no nonzero cell and falls through to `true`. Matches
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::has_boundary`]'s empty-histogram
    /// `true` convention one altitude down on every cardinality-`>=
    /// 0` axis. The empty map sits on the bottom coverage boundary
    /// via the [`Self::tiers_any_observed`]-negation disjunct. Peer
    /// of [`ConfigDiff::kinds_boundary`]'s empty-diff `true` polarity
    /// on the diff altitude in the same projection.
    ///
    /// **Singleton-support convention** — returns `false` on every
    /// fold whose observed support is a single [`ConfigTierKind`]
    /// cell: the support cardinality is `1` (one nonzero and three
    /// zeros on the cardinality-`4` axis), so the single-pass scan
    /// sees a nonzero cell *and* a zero cell and returns `false`.
    /// Every fold with all leaves attributed to only-`Bare`, only-
    /// `Discovered`, only-`Default`, or only-`Custom` is a witness on
    /// the `false` side — singleton-support folds sit strictly off
    /// the two coverage boundaries.
    ///
    /// **Two-tier partial cover convention** — returns `false` on
    /// every fold whose observed support is exactly two
    /// [`ConfigTierKind`] cells: the support cardinality is `2` (two
    /// nonzeros and two zeros on the cardinality-`4` axis), so the
    /// single-pass scan sees both a nonzero and a zero cell and
    /// returns `false`. A fold observing only `Bare` + `Default` is a
    /// witness on the `false` side — sitting on the disjoint
    /// [`Self::tiers_strict_partial_cover`] leg of the distance
    /// ternary.
    ///
    /// **Three-tier partial cover convention** — returns `false` on
    /// every fold whose observed support is exactly three
    /// [`ConfigTierKind`] cells: the support cardinality is `3`
    /// (three nonzeros and one zero on the cardinality-`4` axis), so
    /// the single-pass scan sees both a nonzero and a zero cell and
    /// returns `false`. A fold observing `Bare` + `Default` +
    /// `Custom` (with `Discovered` silent) is a witness on the
    /// `false` side — sitting on the disjoint
    /// [`Self::tiers_singular_gap`] boundary carried by
    /// [`Self::tiers_singular`] in the distance ternary.
    ///
    /// **Uniform four-tier cover convention** — returns `true` on
    /// every fold where each [`ConfigTierKind`] cell was observed at
    /// least once: the support cardinality is `4` (no unobserved
    /// cells on the cardinality-`4` axis), so the single-pass scan
    /// sees only nonzero cells and falls through to `true`. The full-
    /// cover boundary sits at the top of the coverage interval via
    /// the [`Self::tiers_full_cover`] disjunct.
    ///
    /// # Invariants
    ///
    /// - `tiers_boundary() == tier_histogram().has_boundary()` — both
    ///   project the same predicate off the same primitive; the named
    ///   seam is the cube-native routing of the histogram surface.
    /// - `tiers_boundary() ⇔ !tiers_any_observed() ||
    ///   tiers_full_cover()` — the defining union-of-coverage-
    ///   boundaries disjunction on the two named coverage-boundary
    ///   peers. The boundary corner folds the two extreme coverage-
    ///   cardinality corners into one named on-boundary corner.
    /// - `tiers_boundary() == (contributing_tiers_count() == 0 ||
    ///   contributing_tiers_count() ==
    ///   crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>())` always — the
    ///   support-scalar dual-equality surface, without allocating
    ///   `Vec<ConfigTierKind>`. The two equalities are strictly
    ///   disjoint (`0 != 4 = cardinality` on the tier axis).
    /// - `tiers_boundary() == (contributing_tiers_count() == 0 ||
    ///   absent_tiers_count() == 0)` always — the dual-scalar
    ///   equality form on the two named cardinality peers, the
    ///   `contributing + absent == axis_cardinality` invariant
    ///   restated. Peer of the histogram-side dual-scalar equality
    ///   form `hist.distinct_cells() == 0 ||
    ///   hist.unobserved_cells() == 0` pinned one altitude down.
    /// - `!tiers_any_observed() ⇒ tiers_boundary()` always — the
    ///   empty map sits on the boundary via the bottom disjunct.
    /// - `tiers_full_cover() ⇒ tiers_boundary()` always — the full-
    ///   cover fold sits on the boundary via the top disjunct.
    /// - `tiers_boundary() ⇒ !tiers_singular()` on every axis with
    ///   cardinality `>= 2`: the two boundary cardinalities (`0` and
    ///   `cardinality`) sit strictly outside the two singular
    ///   cardinalities (`1` and `cardinality - 1`), so
    ///   `has_boundary` and `has_singular` are pairwise disjoint on
    ///   every cardinality-`>= 2` axis.
    /// - `tiers_boundary() ⇒ !tiers_strict_partial_cover()` always —
    ///   the strict-interior interval `[2, cardinality - 2]` never
    ///   contains the two boundary cardinalities `0` and
    ///   `cardinality`. Non-vacuous at the tier altitude — the two-
    ///   tier partial-cover fixture witnesses
    ///   `tiers_strict_partial_cover == true` and `tiers_boundary ==
    ///   false`, unlike the vacuously-`true` consequent on the
    ///   cardinality-`3` diff altitude where the strict interior is
    ///   empty.
    /// - `(tiers_boundary, tiers_singular, tiers_strict_partial_cover)`
    ///   is a strict ternary partition on every axis with cardinality
    ///   `>= 2` (every tier-altitude implementor today —
    ///   [`ConfigTierKind`] carries four cells). Exactly one leg
    ///   fires on every fold — the distance-from-boundary ternary of
    ///   the 5-corner support-cardinality partition, folding the two
    ///   boundary corners into `has_boundary`, the two singular near-
    ///   boundary corners into `has_singular`, and the boundary-free
    ///   strict interior into `has_strict_partial_cover`. Every leg
    ///   is inhabited at the tier altitude (empty-map / uniform four-
    ///   tier cover fixtures witness the boundary leg, singleton-
    ///   support / three-tier partial cover fixtures witness the
    ///   singular leg, the two-tier partial-cover fixture witnesses
    ///   the strict-interior leg) — a strict advance over the diff
    ///   altitude's degenerate two-way partition
    ///   `(kinds_boundary, kinds_singular)` on the cardinality-`3`
    ///   [`DiffLineKind`] axis.
    /// - **Cross-surface bridge law** —
    ///   `map.tiers_boundary() ==
    ///    map.tier_histogram().support_cardinality_class().is_boundary()`
    ///   always. The class-side projection lands on
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::Empty`] or
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::FullCover`] exactly when
    ///   the histogram-side disjunction fires, and
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::is_boundary`] reads `true`
    ///   on either variant. Peer of the histogram-side bridge
    ///   `axis_histogram_has_boundary_agrees_with_class_is_boundary_for_every_closed_axis_implementor`
    ///   one altitude down, closing the (histogram, class) duality
    ///   on the boundary leg at the tier altitude.
    /// - **Boundary/partial-cover strict-bipartition law** —
    ///   `tiers_boundary()` and the peer partial-cover surface
    ///   `tiers_any_observed() && !tiers_full_cover()` are pointwise
    ///   complementary: exactly one fires on every fold. The named
    ///   boundary corner is the exact complement of the partial-cover
    ///   strict interior at the tier altitude. Peer of the histogram-
    ///   side bipartition law
    ///   `axis_histogram_has_boundary_and_has_partial_cover_form_strict_bipartition_for_every_closed_axis_implementor`
    ///   one altitude down.
    ///
    /// # Cost
    ///
    /// `O(n + k)` where `n = self.inner.len()` (the histogram build)
    /// and `k = crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()` (the
    /// boundary scan). Both are `O(n)` in practice since the tier
    /// axis carries a fixed four-cell cardinality; the returned
    /// `bool` reads one predicate. The scan returns `false` the
    /// *moment* a mixed-parity witness (one zero *and* one nonzero)
    /// has been seen — bounded at two witness cells visited on any
    /// strict-interior histogram — strictly tighter than the
    /// documented open-coded surfaces: no boolean disjunction across
    /// two named coverage-boundary predicates, no full walk of the
    /// counts vector for a scalar equality, no
    /// [`crate::axis_cardinality`] turbofish against a magic
    /// threshold.
    #[must_use]
    pub fn tiers_boundary(&self) -> bool {
        self.tier_histogram().has_boundary()
    }

    /// Returns `true` when this fold's observed [`ConfigTierKind`]
    /// support sits *strictly between* the two coverage boundaries —
    /// at least one tier cell observed *and* at least one tier cell
    /// unobserved ([`Self::tiers_any_observed`] `== true` *and*
    /// [`Self::tiers_full_cover`] `== false`).
    ///
    /// The **partial-cover-tier-counts boolean predicate** on the
    /// tier altitude, the *middle* leg of the coverage trichotomy
    /// `(!tiers_any_observed, tiers_partial_cover, tiers_full_cover)`
    /// — the direct strict-complement of the [`Self::tiers_boundary`]
    /// top-leg corner, folding both singular near-boundary corners
    /// *and* the strict interior into a single "some but not all"
    /// corner without discarding the finer resolution below. Routes
    /// through [`Self::tier_histogram`]`::has_partial_cover`, the
    /// single-pass short-circuiting scan over the fixed-cardinality
    /// counts vector that returns `true` the moment both a zero cell
    /// *and* a nonzero cell have been witnessed, bounded at two
    /// witness cells — strictly tighter than any of the documented
    /// open-coded surfaces one seam over.
    ///
    /// The **partial-cover-tier-counts peer** of the four documented
    /// surface forms consumers previously re-derived inline:
    /// `map.tiers_any_observed() && !map.tiers_full_cover()` (the
    /// structural conjunction-of-negations form on the two named
    /// coverage-boundary peers — one negation, two method calls, and
    /// a boolean and, the surface used verbatim by the pre-existing
    /// bipartition-law test), `0 < map.contributing_tiers_count() &&
    /// map.contributing_tiers_count() <
    /// crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()` (the support-scalar
    /// strict-interval form, which pays for a full-axis scan and
    /// brackets a `usize` against a magic threshold with a turbofish),
    /// `0 < map.absent_tiers_count() && map.absent_tiers_count() <
    /// crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()` (the coverage-gap
    /// dual-scalar strict-interval form), and
    /// `!map.contributing_tiers().is_empty() &&
    /// !map.absent_tiers().is_empty()` (the dual-`Vec` non-emptiness
    /// form, which allocates both support and coverage-gap vectors
    /// just to check their non-emptiness). This lift names the
    /// partial-cover-tier-counts predicate directly at the tier-altitude
    /// surface with a single-pass short-circuiting scan — the typed
    /// boolean every operator-facing *"did the fold observe some tiers
    /// but not all?"* check reads off as a single method call.
    ///
    /// The tier-altitude partial-cover-predicate peer that **climbs
    /// the "partial-cover across altitudes" projection** from the diff
    /// altitude — the *middle* leg of the coverage trichotomy
    /// `(!tiers_any_observed, tiers_partial_cover, tiers_full_cover)`,
    /// lifting the diff-altitude seed [`ConfigDiff::kinds_partial_cover`]
    /// one altitude up. The natural next lifts fan sideways along the
    /// chain altitude's three sub-axes
    /// ([`crate::ConfigSourceChain::layer_kinds_partial_cover`],
    /// [`crate::ConfigSourceChain::file_formats_partial_cover`],
    /// [`crate::ConfigSourceChain::env_prefix_kinds_partial_cover`]
    /// over the corresponding chain histograms). The pattern is the
    /// same at every altitude / sub-axis: fuse the four documented
    /// open-coded surface forms into a single boolean predicate named
    /// at the surface, routed through the shared
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::has_partial_cover`] primitive one
    /// altitude down.
    ///
    /// **Cardinality-`4` reachability at the tier altitude — the
    /// partial-cover corner carries non-vacuous witnesses on every
    /// off-boundary support cardinality.** [`ConfigTierKind`] carries
    /// four cells, so `tiers_partial_cover()` reads `true` on every
    /// singleton-support fold (support cardinality `1` — one nonzero
    /// and three zeros mixed), on every two-tier partial cover
    /// (support cardinality `2` — two nonzeros and two zeros mixed),
    /// and on every three-tier partial cover (support cardinality `3`
    /// — three nonzeros and one zero mixed), and `false` on the empty
    /// map (four zeros — no nonzero witness) and on every uniform
    /// four-tier cover (four nonzeros — no zero witness). Non-vacuous
    /// on *three* off-boundary support cardinalities at the tier
    /// altitude — a strict advance over the diff altitude's two
    /// off-boundary cardinalities on the cardinality-`3` axis, since
    /// the strict-interior leg [`Self::tiers_strict_partial_cover`]
    /// is *reachable* on the cardinality-`4` tier axis (unlike the
    /// vacuously-empty strict interior at the diff altitude).
    ///
    /// **Empty-map convention** — returns `false` on the empty map:
    /// the empty map observes zero cells, so every cell is unobserved
    /// (four zeros on the cardinality-`4` axis) — the single-pass
    /// scan sees no nonzero cell and falls through to `false`. Matches
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::has_partial_cover`]'s empty-histogram
    /// `false` convention one altitude down. The empty map sits on
    /// the [`Self::tiers_boundary`] side (bottom coverage boundary),
    /// strictly complementary to `tiers_partial_cover`. Peer of
    /// [`ConfigDiff::kinds_partial_cover`]'s empty-diff `false`
    /// polarity on the diff altitude in the same projection.
    ///
    /// **Singleton-support convention** — returns `true` on every
    /// fold whose observed support is a single [`ConfigTierKind`]
    /// cell: the support cardinality is `1` (one nonzero and three
    /// zeros on the cardinality-`4` axis), so the single-pass scan
    /// sees a nonzero cell *and* a zero cell and returns `true`.
    /// Every fold with all leaves attributed to only-`Bare`, only-
    /// `Discovered`, only-`Default`, or only-`Custom` is a witness on
    /// the `true` side — singleton-support folds sit inside the
    /// partial-cover middle leg via the [`Self::tiers_singular_support`]
    /// near-boundary corner.
    ///
    /// **Two-tier partial cover convention** — returns `true` on
    /// every fold whose observed support is exactly two
    /// [`ConfigTierKind`] cells: the support cardinality is `2` (two
    /// nonzeros and two zeros on the cardinality-`4` axis), so the
    /// single-pass scan sees both a nonzero and a zero cell and
    /// returns `true`. A fold observing only `Bare` + `Default` is a
    /// witness on the `true` side — sitting on the
    /// [`Self::tiers_strict_partial_cover`] strict-interior leg of the
    /// distance ternary, non-vacuously reachable on the cardinality-
    /// `4` tier axis unlike the vacuously-empty consequent on the
    /// cardinality-`3` diff altitude.
    ///
    /// **Three-tier partial cover convention** — returns `true` on
    /// every fold whose observed support is exactly three
    /// [`ConfigTierKind`] cells: the support cardinality is `3`
    /// (three nonzeros and one zero on the cardinality-`4` axis), so
    /// the single-pass scan sees both a nonzero and a zero cell and
    /// returns `true`. A fold observing `Bare` + `Default` +
    /// `Custom` (with `Discovered` silent) is a witness on the
    /// `true` side — sitting on the [`Self::tiers_singular_gap`]
    /// near-boundary corner of the distance ternary.
    ///
    /// **Uniform four-tier cover convention** — returns `false` on
    /// every fold where each [`ConfigTierKind`] cell was observed at
    /// least once: the support cardinality is `4` (no unobserved
    /// cells on the cardinality-`4` axis), so the single-pass scan
    /// sees only nonzero cells and falls through to `false`. The
    /// full-cover boundary sits at the top of the coverage interval
    /// via the [`Self::tiers_full_cover`] disjunct — strictly outside
    /// the partial-cover middle leg.
    ///
    /// # Invariants
    ///
    /// - `tiers_partial_cover() == tier_histogram().has_partial_cover()`
    ///   — both project the same predicate off the same primitive;
    ///   the named seam is the cube-native routing of the histogram
    ///   surface.
    /// - `tiers_partial_cover() ⇔ tiers_any_observed() &&
    ///   !tiers_full_cover()` — the defining conjunction-of-negations
    ///   form on the two named coverage-boundary peers. The middle-leg
    ///   corner is exactly "at least one observed and at least one
    ///   unobserved".
    /// - `tiers_partial_cover() == (0 < contributing_tiers_count() &&
    ///   contributing_tiers_count() <
    ///   crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>())` always — the
    ///   support-scalar strict-interval surface, without allocating
    ///   `Vec<ConfigTierKind>`.
    /// - `tiers_partial_cover() == (0 < absent_tiers_count() &&
    ///   absent_tiers_count() <
    ///   crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>())` always — the
    ///   coverage-gap dual-scalar strict-interval surface, the
    ///   `distinct_cells + unobserved_cells == axis_cardinality`
    ///   invariant restated on the two named cardinality peers.
    /// - `tiers_partial_cover() == (contributing_tiers_count() > 0 &&
    ///   absent_tiers_count() > 0)` always — the mixed-side dual-
    ///   scalar non-emptiness form, the direct histogram-surface
    ///   `distinct_cells > 0 && unobserved_cells > 0` pin restated
    ///   at the tier altitude.
    /// - `tiers_partial_cover() ⇔ !tiers_boundary()` always — the
    ///   strict bipartition on the coverage-trichotomy fold: the
    ///   named boundary corner is the exact complement of the
    ///   partial-cover strict interior. Peer of the histogram-side
    ///   bipartition law
    ///   `axis_histogram_has_boundary_and_has_partial_cover_form_strict_bipartition_for_every_closed_axis_implementor`
    ///   one altitude down, and of
    ///   [`ConfigDiff::kinds_partial_cover`]'s bipartition peer on
    ///   the diff altitude.
    /// - `tiers_singular_support() ⇒ tiers_partial_cover()` always
    ///   on cardinality-`>= 2` axes: a single observed cell means at
    ///   least one observed (support `1 >= 1`) and at least one
    ///   unobserved (support `1 < cardinality`). Direct pin of the
    ///   histogram-side subsumption
    ///   `has_singular_support ⇒ has_partial_cover` one altitude down.
    /// - `tiers_singular_gap() ⇒ tiers_partial_cover()` always on
    ///   cardinality-`>= 2` axes: a single unobserved cell means at
    ///   least one unobserved and at least one observed. Peer of the
    ///   opposite-end subsumption on the support-cardinality interval.
    /// - `tiers_singular() ⇒ tiers_partial_cover()` always on
    ///   cardinality-`>= 2` axes — the union of the two singular-side
    ///   subsumptions lands the middle-leg singular corners inside
    ///   the partial-cover middle leg.
    /// - `tiers_strict_partial_cover() ⇒ tiers_partial_cover()` always
    ///   — the strict interior sits inside the partial-cover middle
    ///   leg by definition. Non-vacuous at the tier altitude — the
    ///   two-tier partial-cover fixture witnesses both consequent and
    ///   antecedent `true` on the cardinality-`4` tier axis, unlike
    ///   the vacuously-`true` consequent on the cardinality-`3` diff
    ///   altitude where the strict interior is empty. The distance-
    ///   ternary decomposition `(tiers_boundary, tiers_singular,
    ///   tiers_strict_partial_cover)` splits `tiers_partial_cover`
    ///   into its two constituent near-boundary and strict-interior
    ///   legs.
    /// - `tiers_partial_cover() ⇒ tiers_any_observed()` always — the
    ///   partial-cover corner requires at least one observed cell.
    /// - `tiers_partial_cover() ⇒ !tiers_full_cover()` always — the
    ///   partial-cover corner excludes the top coverage boundary.
    /// - **Cross-surface bridge law** —
    ///   `map.tiers_partial_cover() ==
    ///    map.tier_histogram().support_cardinality_class().is_partial_cover()`
    ///   always. The class-side projection lands on
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularSupport`],
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::StrictPartialCover`], or
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::SingularGap`] exactly when
    ///   the histogram-side conjunction fires, and
    ///   [`crate::SupportCardinalityClass::is_partial_cover`] reads
    ///   `true` on any of the three variants. Peer of the histogram-
    ///   side bridge
    ///   `axis_histogram_support_cardinality_class_is_partial_cover_agrees_with_histogram_has_partial_cover_for_every_closed_axis_implementor`
    ///   one altitude down, closing the (histogram, class) duality on
    ///   the partial-cover middle leg at the tier altitude.
    /// - **Coverage-trichotomy partition law** —
    ///   `(!tiers_any_observed, tiers_partial_cover, tiers_full_cover)`
    ///   is a strict ternary partition on every axis with cardinality
    ///   `>= 1` (every tier-altitude implementor today — the
    ///   cardinality-`4` [`ConfigTierKind`] axis). Exactly one leg
    ///   fires on every fold — the coverage trichotomy of the
    ///   `(is_empty, has_partial_cover, is_full_cover)` histogram-side
    ///   partition restated at the tier altitude. Peer of the
    ///   trait-uniform pin
    ///   `axis_histogram_coverage_trichotomy_partitions_every_histogram_for_every_closed_axis_implementor`
    ///   one altitude down. The named seam now carries the middle
    ///   leg of this partition directly at the surface, folding the
    ///   open-coded expression `tiers_any_observed && !tiers_full_cover`
    ///   (the surface used verbatim by the pre-existing bipartition-
    ///   law pin
    ///   [`tests::tiers_boundary_and_tiers_partial_cover_form_strict_bipartition_pointwise`])
    ///   into one named boolean.
    ///
    /// # Cost
    ///
    /// `O(n + k)` where `n = self.inner.len()` (the histogram build)
    /// and `k = crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()` (the
    /// partial-cover scan). Both are `O(n)` in practice since the
    /// tier axis carries a fixed four-cell cardinality; the returned
    /// `bool` reads one predicate. The scan returns `true` the
    /// *moment* a mixed-parity witness (one zero *and* one nonzero)
    /// has been seen — bounded at two witness cells visited on any
    /// strict-interior histogram — strictly tighter than the
    /// documented open-coded surfaces: no boolean conjunction across
    /// two named coverage-boundary predicates, no full walk of the
    /// counts vector for a scalar strict-interval bracket, no
    /// [`crate::axis_cardinality`] turbofish against a magic
    /// threshold, no `Vec<ConfigTierKind>` allocation.
    #[must_use]
    pub fn tiers_partial_cover(&self) -> bool {
        self.tier_histogram().has_partial_cover()
    }

    /// Returns `true` exactly when this fold's observed [`ConfigTierKind`]
    /// histogram has two or more cells tied at the peak leaf count — the
    /// **modally-tied-tier-counts boolean predicate** on the tier
    /// altitude, the direct strict-complement of the strictly-modal-unique
    /// predicate [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_strictly_modally_unique`] on
    /// every non-empty map (both read `false` on the empty map — the
    /// shared boundary below both branches of the strict modal
    /// partition). Routes through
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_modally_tied`] one altitude down: the
    /// single-pass scan over the fixed-cardinality counts vector reading
    /// `self.peak_multiplicity() >= 2` off one predicate, tighter than
    /// either open-coded surface form one seam over.
    ///
    /// The **modally-tied-tier-counts peer** of the two documented
    /// surface forms consumers previously re-derived inline:
    /// `map.tier_histogram().peak_multiplicity() >= 2` (the
    /// multiplicity-scalar inequality form, one method call *plus* a
    /// comparison against a magic `2` threshold), and
    /// `map.tier_histogram().modality_degree().0 >= 2` (the modality-
    /// pair projection-inequality form, reading the modal component of
    /// the fused `(peak_multiplicity, trough_multiplicity)` pair before
    /// the comparison). Both surface forms drift subtly at every
    /// consumer site (scalar vs. pair-component, `>= 2` vs. `!= 1`
    /// after singular-support fixup). This lift names the modally-
    /// tied-tier-counts predicate directly at the tier-altitude surface
    /// as one method call — the typed boolean every operator-facing
    /// *"is the dominant tier uniquely held on this fold, or tied?"*
    /// check reads off at one method call.
    ///
    /// The tier-altitude modality-tie-predicate peer that **climbs the
    /// "modally-tied across altitudes" projection** from the diff
    /// altitude — the modal-side row on top of the closed coverage-
    /// support predicate cube (`low_support`, `high_support`,
    /// `strict_partial_cover`, `singular`, `boundary`, `partial_cover`),
    /// lifting the diff-altitude seed [`ConfigDiff::kinds_modally_tied`]
    /// one altitude up. The natural next lifts fan sideways along the
    /// chain altitude's three sub-axes
    /// ([`crate::ConfigSourceChain::layer_kinds_modally_tied`],
    /// [`crate::ConfigSourceChain::file_formats_modally_tied`],
    /// [`crate::ConfigSourceChain::env_prefix_kinds_modally_tied`] over
    /// the corresponding chain histograms). The pattern is the same at
    /// every altitude / sub-axis: fuse the two open-coded surface forms
    /// (multiplicity-scalar inequality, modality-pair projection-
    /// inequality) into a single boolean predicate named at the
    /// surface, routed through the shared
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_modally_tied`] primitive one altitude
    /// down.
    ///
    /// **Cardinality-`4` reachability at the tier altitude — the
    /// modally-tied corner carries witnesses on both sides.**
    /// [`ConfigTierKind`] carries four cells, so `tiers_modally_tied()`
    /// reads `true` on every fold whose peak leaf count is shared by
    /// two or more observed tier cells (e.g. a fold with one-`Bare` +
    /// one-`Default` leaf where both peak at count `1`, or the uniform
    /// four-tier cover where all four peak at count `1`), and `false`
    /// on the empty map (no observed cell, no peak) and on every fold
    /// with a strictly unique peak (e.g. a fold with all leaves on
    /// `Default` singleton-support, or two-`Bare`+one-`Default` where
    /// `Bare` uniquely peaks at count `2`). Strict advance over the
    /// diff altitude on the same modal-tie surface: three off-peak
    /// support cardinalities carry non-trivial witnesses (support-`2`
    /// tied, support-`3` tied-at-peak, support-`4` full-cover tied)
    /// rather than the two on the cardinality-`3` diff axis.
    ///
    /// **Empty-map convention** — returns `false` on the empty map:
    /// the empty map observes zero cells, so
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::peak_multiplicity`] reads `0` and the
    /// inequality `0 >= 2` fails. Matches
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_modally_tied`]'s empty-histogram
    /// convention one altitude down. The empty-map row on the strict
    /// modal partition pair
    /// `(is_strictly_modally_unique, is_modally_tied)` reads
    /// `(false, false)` — the shared boundary below both branches.
    /// Peer of [`ConfigDiff::kinds_modally_tied`]'s empty-diff `false`
    /// polarity on the diff altitude in the same projection.
    ///
    /// **Singleton-support convention** — returns `false` on every fold
    /// whose observed support is a single [`ConfigTierKind`] cell: the
    /// lone observed cell stands alone at its own peak (no tie-break
    /// to exercise), so `peak_multiplicity` reads `1` and the
    /// inequality `1 >= 2` fails. Every fold with all leaves
    /// attributed to only-`Bare`, only-`Discovered`, only-`Default`,
    /// or only-`Custom` is a witness on the `false` side — the
    /// singleton-support corner is uniformly on the strictly-modal-
    /// unique side of the strict modal partition. Direct pin of the
    /// histogram-side subsumption `has_singular_support ⇒
    /// !is_modally_tied` one altitude down.
    ///
    /// **Uniform four-tier cover convention** — returns `true` on
    /// every fold where each [`ConfigTierKind`] cell was observed at
    /// exactly the same positive count (in particular the fold with
    /// one leaf per tier): the four cells share the same count, so
    /// `peak_multiplicity` reads `4` and the inequality `4 >= 2`
    /// fires. Peer of the histogram-side axis-cover convention one
    /// altitude down, which reads `true` on every implementor with
    /// `axis_cardinality::<A>() >= 2` — the cardinality-`4`
    /// [`ConfigTierKind`] axis honours the general condition.
    ///
    /// **Two-way modal partition on non-empty maps** — on every non-
    /// empty map exactly one of the modal-uniqueness pair fires:
    /// either the peak is uniquely held (strictly-modal-unique fires,
    /// modally-tied does not) or the peak is shared (modally-tied
    /// fires, strictly-modal-unique does not). The empty map sits
    /// below both branches (both read `false`). Direct pin of the
    /// histogram-side strict modal partition
    /// `!is_empty ⇒ is_modally_tied ⇔ !is_strictly_modally_unique`
    /// one altitude down.
    ///
    /// # Invariants
    ///
    /// - `tiers_modally_tied() == tier_histogram().is_modally_tied()`
    ///   — both project the same predicate off the same primitive;
    ///   the named seam is the cube-native routing of the histogram
    ///   surface.
    /// - `tiers_modally_tied() ⇔ tier_histogram().peak_multiplicity() >= 2`
    ///   — the defining multiplicity-scalar inequality form on the
    ///   [`crate::AxisHistogram::peak_multiplicity`] scalar peer, the
    ///   canonical open-coded expression of the predicate one altitude
    ///   down.
    /// - `tiers_modally_tied() ⇔ tier_histogram().modality_degree().0 >= 2`
    ///   — the modality-pair projection-inequality form, reading the
    ///   modal component of the fused
    ///   [`crate::AxisHistogram::modality_degree`] pair before the
    ///   comparison.
    /// - `tiers_modally_tied() ⇒ tiers_any_observed()` always — a
    ///   tied peak requires at least two observed cells, so the empty
    ///   map (zero observed cells) cannot fire. Contrapositively,
    ///   `!tiers_any_observed() ⇒ !tiers_modally_tied()`.
    /// - `tiers_singular_support() ⇒ !tiers_modally_tied()` always —
    ///   a singleton-support fold has exactly one observed cell, so
    ///   the modal level set has cardinality `1` and the tie
    ///   predicate fails. Contrapositively, `tiers_modally_tied() ⇒
    ///   !tiers_singular_support()`: a fired tie predicate means at
    ///   least two observed cells. Direct pin of the histogram-side
    ///   subsumption `has_singular_support ⇒ !is_modally_tied` one
    ///   altitude down.
    /// - `tiers_full_cover() ∧ tiers_balanced() ⇒ tiers_modally_tied()`
    ///   on the cardinality-`>= 2` axis: a full-cover uniform-count
    ///   fold has every cell observed at the same count, so the
    ///   modal level set equals the full axis — the peak multiplicity
    ///   rises to `axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()` which is `4`,
    ///   and the tie predicate fires. Cardinality-`>= 2` witness of
    ///   the uniform-cover corner of the histogram-side subsumption
    ///   tying [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_uniform_count`] and
    ///   [`crate::AxisHistogram::has_singular_support`] on non-empty
    ///   histograms one altitude down.
    /// - **Strict modal partition on non-empty maps** —
    ///   `tiers_any_observed() ⇒ (tiers_modally_tied ⇔
    ///   !tier_histogram().is_strictly_modally_unique())` always. On
    ///   every non-empty map exactly one of
    ///   `(tiers_modally_tied, tier_histogram().is_strictly_modally_unique())`
    ///   fires; both read `false` on the empty map — the shared
    ///   boundary below both branches. Direct pin of the histogram-
    ///   side strict modal partition one altitude down.
    ///
    /// # Cost
    ///
    /// `O(n + k)` where `n = self.inner.len()` (the histogram build)
    /// and `k = crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()` (the
    /// peak-multiplicity scan). Both are `O(n)` in practice since the
    /// tier axis carries a fixed four-cell cardinality; the returned
    /// `bool` reads one predicate — the peak scan walks the counts
    /// vector once and counts cells matching the max, then reads
    /// `multiplicity >= 2` off one comparison. Strictly tighter than
    /// the two documented open-coded surfaces one seam over (no
    /// exposed `>= 2` magic threshold at the consumer site, no
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::modality_degree`] fused-pair build for
    /// a single-component projection).
    #[must_use]
    pub fn tiers_modally_tied(&self) -> bool {
        self.tier_histogram().is_modally_tied()
    }

    /// Returns `true` exactly when this fold's observed [`ConfigTierKind`]
    /// histogram has two or more cells tied at the trough leaf count — the
    /// **antimodally-tied-tier-counts boolean predicate** on the tier
    /// altitude, the direct strict-complement of the strictly-antimodal-
    /// unique predicate [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_strictly_antimodally_unique`]
    /// on every non-empty fold (both read `false` on the empty map — the
    /// shared boundary below both branches of the strict antimodal
    /// partition). Routes through
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_antimodally_tied`] one altitude down: the
    /// single-pass scan over the fixed-cardinality counts vector reading
    /// `self.trough_multiplicity() >= 2` off one predicate, tighter than
    /// either open-coded surface form one seam over.
    ///
    /// The **antimodally-tied-tier-counts peer** of the two documented
    /// surface forms consumers previously re-derived inline:
    /// `map.tier_histogram().trough_multiplicity() >= 2` (the
    /// multiplicity-scalar inequality form, one method call *plus* a
    /// comparison against a magic `2` threshold), and
    /// `map.tier_histogram().modality_degree().1 >= 2` (the modality-
    /// pair projection-inequality form, reading the antimodal component
    /// of the fused `(peak_multiplicity, trough_multiplicity)` pair
    /// before the comparison). Both surface forms drift subtly at every
    /// consumer site (scalar vs. pair-component, `>= 2` vs. `!= 1` after
    /// singular-support fixup). This lift names the antimodally-tied-
    /// tier-counts predicate directly at the tier-altitude surface as
    /// one method call — the typed boolean every operator-facing
    /// *"is the rarest tier uniquely held on this fold, or is the
    /// declaration-order tie-break exercised?"* check reads off at one
    /// method call.
    ///
    /// The tier-altitude antimodal-tie-predicate peer that **climbs the
    /// "antimodally-tied across altitudes" projection** from the diff
    /// altitude — the antimodal-side row on the modality surface,
    /// complementary to the just-closed modally-tied projection: the
    /// modal-side row of the modality classifier pair
    /// `(is_modally_tied, is_antimodally_tied)` is already lifted at
    /// every altitude / sub-axis of the fully-closed cube; this climb
    /// lifts the antimodal-side diff-altitude seed
    /// [`ConfigDiff::kinds_antimodally_tied`] one altitude up. The
    /// natural next lifts fan sideways along the chain altitude's three
    /// sub-axes
    /// ([`crate::ConfigSourceChain::layer_kinds_antimodally_tied`],
    /// [`crate::ConfigSourceChain::file_formats_antimodally_tied`],
    /// [`crate::ConfigSourceChain::env_prefix_kinds_antimodally_tied`]
    /// over the corresponding chain histograms). The pattern is the
    /// same at every altitude / sub-axis: fuse the two open-coded
    /// surface forms (multiplicity-scalar inequality, modality-pair
    /// projection-inequality) into a single boolean predicate named at
    /// the surface, routed through the shared
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_antimodally_tied`] primitive one
    /// altitude down.
    ///
    /// **Cardinality-`4` reachability at the tier altitude — the
    /// antimodally-tied corner carries witnesses on more support
    /// cardinalities.** [`ConfigTierKind`] carries four cells, so
    /// `tiers_antimodally_tied()` reads `true` on every fold whose
    /// trough leaf count is shared by two or more observed tier cells
    /// (e.g. a fold with one-`Bare` + one-`Default` leaf where both
    /// sit at count `1`, a fold with two-`Bare`+one-`Default`+one-
    /// `Custom` where `Default` *and* `Custom` share the trough at
    /// count `1`, or the uniform four-tier cover where all four sit at
    /// count `1`), and `false` on the empty map (no observed cell, no
    /// trough) and on every fold with a strictly unique trough (e.g.
    /// a fold with all leaves on `Default` singleton-support, or two-
    /// `Bare`+one-`Default` where `Default` uniquely sits at count `1`
    /// while `Bare` peaks at `2`). Strict advance over the diff
    /// altitude on the same antimodal-tie surface: three off-trough
    /// support cardinalities carry non-trivial witnesses (support-`2`
    /// tied-at-`1`, support-`3` with two-way trough tie, support-`4`
    /// full-cover tied) rather than the two on the cardinality-`3`
    /// diff axis.
    ///
    /// **Empty-map convention** — returns `false` on the empty map:
    /// the empty map observes zero cells, so
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::trough_multiplicity`] reads `0` and the
    /// inequality `0 >= 2` fails. Matches
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_antimodally_tied`]'s empty-histogram
    /// convention one altitude down. The empty-map row on the strict
    /// antimodal partition pair
    /// `(is_strictly_antimodally_unique, is_antimodally_tied)` reads
    /// `(false, false)` — the shared boundary below both branches.
    /// Peer of [`ConfigDiff::kinds_antimodally_tied`]'s empty-diff
    /// `false` polarity on the diff altitude in the same projection.
    ///
    /// **Singleton-support convention** — returns `false` on every fold
    /// whose observed support is a single [`ConfigTierKind`] cell: the
    /// lone observed cell stands alone at its own trough (peak and
    /// trough coincide), so
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::trough_multiplicity`] reads `1` and the
    /// inequality `1 >= 2` fails. Every fold with all leaves
    /// attributed to only-`Bare`, only-`Discovered`, only-`Default`,
    /// or only-`Custom` is a witness on the `false` side — the
    /// singleton-support corner is uniformly on the strictly-antimodal-
    /// unique side of the strict antimodal partition. Direct pin of the
    /// histogram-side subsumption `has_singular_support ⇒
    /// !is_antimodally_tied` one altitude down.
    ///
    /// **Uniform four-tier cover convention** — returns `true` on every
    /// fold where each [`ConfigTierKind`] cell was observed at exactly
    /// the same positive count (in particular the fold with one leaf
    /// per tier): the four cells share the same count, so
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::trough_multiplicity`] reads `4` and the
    /// inequality `4 >= 2` fires. Peer of the histogram-side axis-cover
    /// convention one altitude down, which reads `true` on every
    /// implementor with `axis_cardinality::<A>() >= 2` — the
    /// cardinality-`4` [`ConfigTierKind`] axis honours the general
    /// condition.
    ///
    /// **Two-way antimodal partition on non-empty maps** — on every
    /// non-empty map exactly one of the antimodal-uniqueness pair
    /// fires: either the trough is uniquely held (strictly-antimodal-
    /// unique fires, antimodally-tied does not) or the trough is
    /// shared (antimodally-tied fires, strictly-antimodal-unique does
    /// not). The empty map sits below both branches (both read
    /// `false`). Direct pin of the histogram-side strict antimodal
    /// partition `!is_empty ⇒ is_antimodally_tied ⇔
    /// !is_strictly_antimodally_unique` one altitude down.
    ///
    /// **Modal / antimodal collapse on uniform-count maps** — on every
    /// uniform-count non-empty map the modal and antimodal level sets
    /// coincide with the support, so
    /// `tiers_antimodally_tied ⇔ tiers_modally_tied` — the classifier
    /// pair collapses to a single boolean, the multi-cell-support
    /// witness. Direct pin of the histogram-side collapse law
    /// `is_uniform_count ∧ !is_empty ⇒ is_antimodally_tied ⇔
    /// is_modally_tied` one altitude down, peer of the same collapse
    /// pinned at the diff altitude by
    /// [`ConfigDiff::kinds_antimodally_tied`].
    ///
    /// # Invariants
    ///
    /// - `tiers_antimodally_tied() == tier_histogram().is_antimodally_tied()`
    ///   — both project the same predicate off the same primitive; the
    ///   named seam is the cube-native routing of the histogram surface.
    /// - `tiers_antimodally_tied() ⇔ tier_histogram().trough_multiplicity() >= 2`
    ///   — the defining multiplicity-scalar inequality form on the
    ///   [`crate::AxisHistogram::trough_multiplicity`] scalar peer, the
    ///   canonical open-coded expression of the predicate one altitude
    ///   down.
    /// - `tiers_antimodally_tied() ⇔ tier_histogram().modality_degree().1 >= 2`
    ///   — the modality-pair projection-inequality form, reading the
    ///   antimodal component of the fused
    ///   [`crate::AxisHistogram::modality_degree`] pair before the
    ///   comparison.
    /// - `tiers_antimodally_tied() ⇒ tiers_any_observed()` always — a
    ///   tied trough requires at least two observed cells, so the
    ///   empty map (zero observed cells) cannot fire. Contrapositively,
    ///   `!tiers_any_observed() ⇒ !tiers_antimodally_tied()`.
    /// - `tiers_singular_support() ⇒ !tiers_antimodally_tied()` always
    ///   — a singleton-support fold has exactly one observed cell, so
    ///   the antimodal level set has cardinality `1` and the tie
    ///   predicate fails. Contrapositively, `tiers_antimodally_tied()
    ///   ⇒ !tiers_singular_support()`: a fired tie predicate means at
    ///   least two observed cells. Direct pin of the histogram-side
    ///   subsumption `has_singular_support ⇒ !is_antimodally_tied` one
    ///   altitude down.
    /// - `tiers_full_cover() ∧ tiers_balanced() ⇒ tiers_antimodally_tied()`
    ///   on the cardinality-`>= 2` axis: a full-cover uniform-count
    ///   fold has every cell observed at the same count, so the
    ///   antimodal level set equals the full axis — the trough
    ///   multiplicity rises to `axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()`
    ///   which is `4`, and the tie predicate fires. Cardinality-`>= 2`
    ///   witness of the uniform-cover corner of the histogram-side
    ///   subsumption tying [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_uniform_count`]
    ///   and [`crate::AxisHistogram::has_singular_support`] on non-
    ///   empty histograms one altitude down.
    /// - **Strict antimodal partition on non-empty maps** —
    ///   `tiers_any_observed() ⇒ (tiers_antimodally_tied ⇔
    ///   !tier_histogram().is_strictly_antimodally_unique())` always.
    ///   On every non-empty map exactly one of
    ///   `(tiers_antimodally_tied, tier_histogram().is_strictly_antimodally_unique())`
    ///   fires; both read `false` on the empty map — the shared
    ///   boundary below both branches. Direct pin of the histogram-
    ///   side strict antimodal partition one altitude down.
    /// - **Modal / antimodal collapse on uniform-count maps** —
    ///   `tiers_balanced() ∧ tiers_any_observed() ⇒
    ///   tiers_antimodally_tied() ⇔ tiers_modally_tied()`. On every
    ///   uniform-count non-empty map the two tie predicates collapse
    ///   to the same value. Direct pin of the histogram-side collapse
    ///   `is_uniform_count ∧ !is_empty ⇒ is_antimodally_tied ⇔
    ///   is_modally_tied` one altitude down, peer of the same collapse
    ///   pinned at the diff altitude by
    ///   [`ConfigDiff::kinds_antimodally_tied`].
    ///
    /// # Cost
    ///
    /// `O(n + k)` where `n = self.inner.len()` (the histogram build)
    /// and `k = crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()` (the
    /// trough-multiplicity scan). Both are `O(n)` in practice since the
    /// tier axis carries a fixed four-cell cardinality; the returned
    /// `bool` reads one predicate — the trough scan walks the counts
    /// vector once and counts cells matching the strictly-positive
    /// minimum, then reads `multiplicity >= 2` off one comparison.
    /// Strictly tighter than the two documented open-coded surfaces
    /// one seam over (no exposed `>= 2` magic threshold at the
    /// consumer site, no [`crate::AxisHistogram::modality_degree`]
    /// fused-pair build for a single-component projection).
    #[must_use]
    pub fn tiers_antimodally_tied(&self) -> bool {
        self.tier_histogram().is_antimodally_tied()
    }

    /// Returns `true` exactly when this fold's observed [`ConfigTierKind`]
    /// histogram has exactly one cell holding the peak leaf count — the
    /// **strictly-modally-unique-tier-counts boolean predicate** on the
    /// tier altitude, the direct strict-complement of the modally-tied
    /// predicate [`Self::tiers_modally_tied`] on every non-empty fold
    /// (both read `false` on the empty map — the shared boundary below
    /// both branches of the strict modal partition). Routes through
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_strictly_modally_unique`] one altitude
    /// down: the single-pass scan over the fixed-cardinality counts
    /// vector reading `self.peak_multiplicity() == 1` off one predicate,
    /// tighter than either open-coded surface form one seam over.
    ///
    /// The **strictly-modally-unique-tier-counts peer** of the two
    /// documented surface forms consumers previously re-derived inline:
    /// `map.tier_histogram().peak_multiplicity() == 1` (the
    /// multiplicity-scalar equality form, one method call *plus* a
    /// comparison against a magic `1` threshold), and
    /// `map.tier_histogram().modality_degree().0 == 1` (the modality-
    /// pair projection-equality form, reading the modal component of
    /// the fused `(peak_multiplicity, trough_multiplicity)` pair before
    /// the equality). Both surface forms drift subtly at every consumer
    /// site (scalar vs. pair-component, `== 1` vs. `!= 2` after
    /// singular-support fixup). This lift names the strictly-modally-
    /// unique-tier-counts predicate directly at the tier-altitude
    /// surface as one method call — the typed boolean every operator-
    /// facing *"is the dominant tier uniquely held on this fold, or is
    /// the declaration-order tie-break exercised?"* check reads off at
    /// one method call, on the strict-uniqueness side of the strict
    /// modal partition.
    ///
    /// The tier-altitude strict-modal-uniqueness predicate peer that
    /// **climbs the "strictly-modally-unique across altitudes"
    /// projection** from the diff altitude — the strict-uniqueness row
    /// on top of the closed modality-tie boolean pair
    /// (`tiers_modally_tied`, `tiers_antimodally_tied`) at every
    /// altitude / sub-axis of the fully-closed cube; this climb lifts
    /// the diff-altitude seed [`ConfigDiff::kinds_strictly_modally_unique`]
    /// one altitude up. The natural next lifts fan sideways along the
    /// chain altitude's three sub-axes
    /// ([`crate::ConfigSourceChain::layer_kinds_strictly_modally_unique`],
    /// [`crate::ConfigSourceChain::file_formats_strictly_modally_unique`],
    /// [`crate::ConfigSourceChain::env_prefix_kinds_strictly_modally_unique`]
    /// over the corresponding chain histograms). The pattern is the
    /// same at every altitude / sub-axis: fuse the two open-coded
    /// surface forms (multiplicity-scalar equality, modality-pair
    /// projection-equality) into a single boolean predicate named at
    /// the surface, routed through the shared
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_strictly_modally_unique`] primitive
    /// one altitude down.
    ///
    /// **Cardinality-`4` reachability at the tier altitude — the
    /// strictly-modally-unique corner carries witnesses across more
    /// support cardinalities.** [`ConfigTierKind`] carries four cells,
    /// so `tiers_strictly_modally_unique()` reads `true` on every fold
    /// whose peak leaf count is uniquely held by exactly one observed
    /// tier cell (e.g. a fold with all leaves on `Default` singleton-
    /// support, or two-`Bare`+one-`Default` where `Bare` uniquely peaks
    /// at count `2`), and `false` on the empty map (no observed cell,
    /// no peak), on every two-tier tied-at-count-`1` fold (`Bare` +
    /// `Default` both at `1`), on every three-tier tied-at-count-`1`
    /// fold (`Bare` + `Default` + `Custom` all at `1`), and on the
    /// uniform four-tier cover where all four cells sit at count `1`.
    /// Strict advance over the diff altitude on the same strict-modal-
    /// uniqueness surface: two off-peak support cardinalities carry
    /// tied-peak witnesses (support-`3` three-tier tied-at-`1`,
    /// support-`4` full-cover tied) that are *reachable* on the
    /// cardinality-`4` tier axis but do not exist on the cardinality-`3`
    /// diff altitude.
    ///
    /// **Empty-map convention** — returns `false` on the empty map: the
    /// empty map observes zero cells, so
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::peak_multiplicity`] reads `0` and the
    /// equality `0 == 1` fails. Matches
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_strictly_modally_unique`]'s empty-
    /// histogram convention one altitude down. The empty-map row on
    /// the strict modal partition pair
    /// `(is_strictly_modally_unique, is_modally_tied)` reads
    /// `(false, false)` — the shared boundary below both branches.
    /// Peer of [`ConfigDiff::kinds_strictly_modally_unique`]'s empty-
    /// diff `false` polarity on the diff altitude in the same
    /// projection.
    ///
    /// **Singleton-support convention** — returns `true` on every fold
    /// whose observed support is a single [`ConfigTierKind`] cell: the
    /// lone observed cell stands alone at its own peak (no tie-break
    /// to exercise), so `peak_multiplicity` reads `1` and the equality
    /// `1 == 1` fires. Every fold with all leaves attributed to only-
    /// `Bare`, only-`Discovered`, only-`Default`, or only-`Custom` is
    /// a witness on the `true` side — the singleton-support corner is
    /// uniformly on the strictly-modally-unique side of the strict
    /// modal partition. Direct pin of the histogram-side subsumption
    /// `has_singular_support ⇒ is_strictly_modally_unique` one
    /// altitude down.
    ///
    /// **Uniform four-tier cover convention** — returns `false` on
    /// every fold where each [`ConfigTierKind`] cell was observed at
    /// exactly the same positive count (in particular the fold with
    /// one leaf per tier): the four cells share the same count, so
    /// `peak_multiplicity` reads `4` and the equality `4 == 1` fails.
    /// Peer of the histogram-side axis-cover convention one altitude
    /// down, which reads `false` on every implementor with
    /// `axis_cardinality::<A>() >= 2` — the cardinality-`4`
    /// [`ConfigTierKind`] axis honours the general condition.
    ///
    /// **Two-way modal partition on non-empty maps** — on every non-
    /// empty map exactly one of the modal-uniqueness pair
    /// `(tiers_strictly_modally_unique, tiers_modally_tied)` fires:
    /// either the peak is uniquely held (strictly-modally-unique
    /// fires, modally-tied does not) or the peak is shared (modally-
    /// tied fires, strictly-modally-unique does not). The empty map
    /// sits below both branches (both read `false`). Direct pin of the
    /// histogram-side strict modal partition
    /// `!is_empty ⇒ is_strictly_modally_unique ⇔ !is_modally_tied`
    /// one altitude down.
    ///
    /// # Invariants
    ///
    /// - `tiers_strictly_modally_unique() == tier_histogram().is_strictly_modally_unique()`
    ///   — both project the same predicate off the same primitive; the
    ///   named seam is the cube-native routing of the histogram surface.
    /// - `tiers_strictly_modally_unique() ⇔ tier_histogram().peak_multiplicity() == 1`
    ///   — the defining multiplicity-scalar equality form on the
    ///   [`crate::AxisHistogram::peak_multiplicity`] scalar peer, the
    ///   canonical open-coded expression of the predicate one altitude
    ///   down.
    /// - `tiers_strictly_modally_unique() ⇔ tier_histogram().modality_degree().0 == 1`
    ///   — the modality-pair projection-equality form, reading the
    ///   modal component of the fused
    ///   [`crate::AxisHistogram::modality_degree`] pair before the
    ///   equality.
    /// - `tiers_strictly_modally_unique() ⇒ tiers_any_observed()`
    ///   always — a strictly-unique peak requires at least one observed
    ///   cell, so the empty map (zero observed cells) cannot fire.
    ///   Contrapositively, `!tiers_any_observed() ⇒
    ///   !tiers_strictly_modally_unique()`.
    /// - `tiers_singular_support() ⇒ tiers_strictly_modally_unique()`
    ///   always — a singleton-support fold has exactly one observed
    ///   cell as the sole member of the modal level set, so the
    ///   uniqueness predicate fires. Direct pin of the histogram-side
    ///   subsumption `has_singular_support ⇒ is_strictly_modally_unique`
    ///   one altitude down.
    /// - **Strict modal partition on non-empty maps** —
    ///   `tiers_any_observed() ⇒ (tiers_strictly_modally_unique ⇔
    ///   !tiers_modally_tied())` always. On every non-empty map exactly
    ///   one of `(tiers_strictly_modally_unique, tiers_modally_tied)`
    ///   fires; both read `false` on the empty map — the shared
    ///   boundary below both branches. Direct pin of the histogram-
    ///   side strict-modal-partition law one altitude down, phrased as
    ///   an XOR on the two named seams at the tier-altitude surface.
    /// - `tiers_full_cover() ∧ tiers_balanced() ⇒
    ///   !tiers_strictly_modally_unique()` on the cardinality-`>= 2`
    ///   axis: a full-cover uniform-count fold has every cell observed
    ///   at the same count, so the modal level set equals the full
    ///   axis — the peak multiplicity rises to
    ///   `axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()` which is `4`, and the
    ///   uniqueness predicate fails. Cardinality-`>= 2` witness of the
    ///   uniform-cover corner of the histogram-side subsumption tying
    ///   [`crate::AxisHistogram::is_uniform_count`] and
    ///   [`crate::AxisHistogram::has_singular_support`] on non-empty
    ///   histograms one altitude down.
    ///
    /// # Cost
    ///
    /// `O(n + k)` where `n = self.inner.len()` (the histogram build)
    /// and `k = crate::axis_cardinality::<ConfigTierKind>()` (the
    /// peak-multiplicity scan). Both are `O(n)` in practice since the
    /// tier axis carries a fixed four-cell cardinality; the returned
    /// `bool` reads one predicate — the peak scan walks the counts
    /// vector once and counts cells matching the max, then reads
    /// `multiplicity == 1` off one comparison. Strictly tighter than
    /// the two documented open-coded surfaces one seam over (no
    /// exposed `== 1` magic threshold at the consumer site, no
    /// [`crate::AxisHistogram::modality_degree`] fused-pair build for
    /// a single-component projection).
    #[must_use]
    pub fn tiers_strictly_modally_unique(&self) -> bool {
        self.tier_histogram().is_strictly_modally_unique()
    }

